  <source>Guy's and St Thomas' NHS Foundation Trust</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      'ThRIL' aims to explore the feasibility, safety and efficacy of TR002, a regulatory cell
      therapy, as adjunct immunosuppressive treatment in the context of liver transplantation
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Stage I: To evaluate the safety of administering TR002 to liver transplant recipients.

      Stage II: To evaluate the efficacy of TR002 administration in allowing for the
      discontinuation of immunosuppressive therapy in liver transplant recipients.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
